    "body": "## Description\n\nWhen trying to authenticate with a username containing special characters like `@`, `+`, or `-`, the authentication process fails with a 400 error.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Navigate to the login page\n2. Enter username: `test-user@domain.com`\n3. Enter valid password\n4. Click \"Sign In\"\n5. Observe error message: \"Invalid username format\"\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nAuthentication should succeed with usernames containing special characters, as these are valid in many systems.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nAuthentication fails with an error message about invalid username format.\n\n## Environment\n\n- Browser: Chrome 120.0.6099.71\n- OS: macOS 14.2.1\n- App Version: 1.9.5\n\n## Additional Context\n\nThis might be related to the recent changes in PR #42 that updated the authentication system. The validation regex might be too restrictive.\n\n## Error Logs\n\n```\n2024-01-15 10:15:28 ERROR [auth.validation] Invalid username format: test-user@domain.com\n2024-01-15 10:15:28 ERROR [auth.oauth] Username validation failed for user registration\n```",
